<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-23T15:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-23T15:36:00-05:00" n="235" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">814.51/294: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-23T14:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">May 23,
                                            1919, 2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        May 25, 245 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>See despatch number 506 dated April 30, 1918, enclosure number
                                    1.<note n="9" xml:id="d235fn9"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_271">p. 271</ref>.</note></p>
                            <p>A commission has just been appointed for the purpose of devising
                                means whereby a national bank may be established.</p>
                            <p>I am reliably informed that the proposed issue of 60,000,000 pesos
                                has been canceled and that only 10,000,000 will be given the Banco
                                Americano.</p>
                            <p>In the opinion of bankers this renewal of interest in the national
                                bank indicates tendency in favor of a foreign loan since it is not
                                felt the necessary capital could be commanded locally for its
                                establishment.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>